parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in repairs, leaving vehicles on the road with potentially deadly defects.
symptoms: Receipt of recall notification
but parts are not available for repair
leading to a delay in fixing the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle pinion nut can cause the rear axle bearings to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Noise coming from the rear of the vehicle
vibration
and loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission/driveline issues can cause loss of power, sudden acceleration, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle lurches forward
sudden loss of power
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the 4-wheel drive system can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Inadvertent shifting from 4-wheel drive to 4-wheel low
loss of power
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause loss of essential vehicle functions, leading to accidents and inconvenience.
symptoms: Overhead console
dash
and radio malfunctioning
and turn signals flashing randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor warranties and recalls can lead to financial losses and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Difficulty getting repairs done under warranty
and lack of communication from manufacturers and dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel pump short circuit can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not turn on after pumping gas
gas spills from underneath the vehicle
and the starter motor does not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A dead 12V battery can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery is dead within 24 hours of not being driven
all lights are off
and keys are removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the overhead control module can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to a loss of vehicle functionality and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The overhead control module has failed multiple times
and the manufacturer is not covering the repair under warranty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hybrid vehicle drop dead issue can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle drops dead while driving
often at high speeds
and the dealership is unable to diagnose the cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system malfunction can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to a loss of vehicle functionality and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard lights do not work
the gas tank cannot be filled up all the way
and the vehicle shuts off at any given time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A trip computer malfunction can cause the battery to die and other electrical systems to malfunction, leading to a loss of vehicle functionality and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The trip computer illuminates red and malfunctions
causing the battery to die.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure - Check Valve Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system, specifically the check valve, can cause the vehicle to stall repeatedly, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents. Additionally, fuel splashing out during fueling can create a fire hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls repeatedly after filling up the gas tank
often requiring multiple cycles of starting and stalling before it will continue to run. The problem is more severe in cold weather. Fuel splashes out during fueling
and a strong gas smell is present after filling up.
